result.execSummary:
The defendant Dillon D Wincapaw was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting/Failing to Stop/Fleeing, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(2t).
  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Dillon D Wincapaw in court with attorney Mark P Murphy.  Bryan C. Bayer appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State files an amended information.  Defendant enters a plea of no contest to counts 1 & 3 on the amended information.  Defendant enters a plea of guilty to count 2 on the amended information.  Court finds the defendant guilty of counts 1-3 as set forth in the amended information.    
Attorney Bayer makes recommendations to the court regarding sentencing.  Attorney Murphy makes statements to the court regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements to the court.  

The Court Orders the Following: COUNT #1

Imposed Sentence of:
30 Days Huber with STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.  (Credit - 0 days).  Defendant to report to Huber facility by 5 p.m. on May 29, 2016.  CONCURRENT WITH COUNTS 2 & 3.

COSTS:  $243.00 to be paid within 60 days, alternate 19 days jail if not paid.  (19 days is inclusive of all 3 counts and DNA surcharge)

DNA Surcharge: $200.00 to be paid within 60 days.
